NAME
    gcloud alpha container binauthz authorities public-keys update - update a
        public key on an Attestation Authority

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha container binauthz authorities public-keys update
        PUBLIC_KEY_FINGERPRINT --authority=AUTHORITY [--comment=COMMENT]
        [--public-key-file=PUBLIC_KEY_FILE] [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) Update a public key on an Attestation Authority.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     PUBLIC_KEY_FINGERPRINT
        The fingerprint of the public key to update.

REQUIRED FLAGS
     Authority resource - The authority on which the public key should be
     updated. This represents a Cloud resource. (NOTE) Some attributes are not
     given arguments in this group but can be set in other ways. To set the
     [project] attribute: provide the flag [--authority] on the command line
     with a fully specified name; provide the flag [--project] on the command
     line; set the property [core/project]. This must be specified.

       --authority=AUTHORITY
          The ID of the authority or a fully qualified identifier for the
          authority.

OPTIONAL FLAGS
     --comment=COMMENT
        The comment describing the public key.

     --public-key-file=PUBLIC_KEY_FILE
        The path to the file containing the new ASCII-armored PGP public key.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

NOTES
    This command is an internal implementation detail and may change or
    disappear without notice. This command is currently in ALPHA and may change
    without notice. Usually, users of ALPHA commands and flags need to apply
    for access, agree to applicable terms, and have their projects whitelisted.
    Contact Google or sign up on a product's page for ALPHA access. Product
    pages can be found at https://cloud.google.com/products/.

